title: How to Force Eject a Disc Stuck in Your Xbox 360
category_hierarchy: Video Game Console Maintenance and Repair

steps.headline: Remove the faceplate from the console.
steps.description: With the console laying flat, use a flat-head screwdriver to pop in the tab inward on the right side of the console.

steps.headline: Straighten out a length of paper clip as best you can.
Place the long end of the paper clip in the hole on the very left.
steps.description: Note: It's more of a "semi" hole and there is one directly to the right of it.

steps.headline: Using a flashlight, place the end of the paper clip in the teeth on the right side of the gears and push.
steps.description: The tray should slide open a little, and from there you can open and close the tray with your hand.
